Steps required to add various Refplat ISOs manually after initial CML install.

1  Download the particular Refplas ISO you require from https://learningnetworkstore.cisco.com/myaccount;

      refplat-20250616-fcs.iso
      refplat-20250718-ise.iso
      refplat-20250718-supplemental.iso

2  Extract Refplat file to USB drive

3  Navigate to the CML2 Cockpit;

      https://cml-controller:9090/

4  Open the terminal

      type "lsblk" to discover the name of your USB drive (my USB drive is labeled sdb1)

5  Mount the USB drive as /cdrom

      sudo mkdir -p /mnt/usb

      sudo mount /dev/sdb1 /mnt/usb

    Varify ISO is in /mnt/usb/
  
      ls /mnt/usb/refplat-20250718-supplemental.iso

      sudo mkdir -p /cdrom

      sudo mount -o loop /mnt/usb/refplat-20250718-supplemental.iso /cdrom

      mount | grep cdrom

      sudo systemctl restart virl2.target

6  Navigate to CML2 on the cockpit and click the "Copy Refplat ISO" button

      Once files have been copied, all images should now appear in CML > Tools > Node and Image Definitions

7  Return to the CML cockpit terminal complete the clean up:

      sudo umount /cdrom

      sudo umount /mnt/usb

      sudo rmdir /cdrom /mnt/usb